Subject: Re: [T2] lube pilot bearing

On Fri, 2 Jan 2004, Richard Atwell wrote:

> I found this neat tip at aricooled.net wrt distributor grease:

> > This high temperature grease won't fly out onto your points like vaseline, or
> > this on every 3k miles. This is also GREAT for input shaft and throwout
> > bearings (inside the gland nut or flywheel), since it won't get hot and then
> > fly out onto your clutch! Also used for generator or alternator bearings. This
> > is a must for your garage.

> Has anyone tried this on the pilot bearing?

I have a tube of Bosch distributor grease and I have used it on pilot
bearings and shaft.  It works as advertised.

I wouldn't use it for any high-speed bearing, like alternator bearings, as
it is not made for high speed use.

George Lyle
